{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"criteria":[{"citation":{"description":"Ticket comment by Joe Oakhart: 'SPIKE RESULT: PASS (definitive). Ran headless Claude Code v2.1.211 in an isolated temp dir with CLAUDE.md = @AGENTS.md and AGENTS.md holding a canary token; the model returned the canary VERBATIM with NO approval prompt. Version tested: claude 2.1.211.' Additionally, CLAUDE.md line 3 shows @AGENTS.md import in production, corroborating that the mechanism was validated and adopted.","kind":"source"},"criterion":"Confirmed whether `@AGENTS.md` in `CLAUDE.md` loads `AGENTS.md` into context in the installed Claude Code build; result recorded as a comment on this ticket with the exact version tested (PASS/FAIL + `claude --version`).","kind":"operator-attested","met":true},{"citation":{"description":"The spike result was PASS, so the FAIL branch does not apply. The ticket body and comment both confirm 'No symlink fallback needed' and downstream stories (6642 and 5b01) build on the proven @AGENTS.md import mechanism.","kind":"source"},"criterion":"If FAIL, the fallback mechanism (symlink vs. content-copy-with-sync-test) is chosen and noted so the AGENTS.md story uses it.","kind":"operator-attested","met":true},{"citation":{"description":"Directory listing shows no stray spike files (e.g., no throwaway AGENTS.md or CLAUDE.md from a scratch test). The spike was done in a throwaway temp dir per the comment. The AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md in the repo root are production files, not spike artifacts. No unexpected temp/scratch files visible in the repo.","kind":"file","path":"."},"criterion":"No stray spike files left in the repo working tree (git status --porcelain clean after the spike).","kind":"operator-attested","met":true}],"finding